When I was 12 years old, every Saturday morning I remember waking up and ask my father to go together to buy the newspaper. I wasn't really interested in local news, rather to the weekly real estate page.

With the years, my passion towards real estate remained intact even if life took me towards a different career path. 
At age 33, after years spent in tech whether I was leading marketing team for upcoming startups or planning global demand generation strategies for corporate, I decided to MAKE THE MOVE, quit my job, throw away everything stable in my life and move to NYC to become a Real Estate Broker.

Today, after slightly less then one year in the business, tens of completed deals and 10x more rejections, I'm beyond excited to officially announce that I've joined Compass, the Nation's most innovative luxury brokerage.

I wanted to thank you all for the support and invite you to reach out whenever you have ANY real estate related question. I'M YOUR GUY!

Onward and upward.
